statistics.name: assists
statistics.description: The number of times a player who passes the ball to a teammate in a way that leads to a score by field goal, meaning that he or she was "assisting" in the basket. There is some judgment involved in deciding whether a passer should be credited with an assist.

statistics.name: turnovers
statistics.description: The number of times a player loses possession to the other team.

statistics.name: assistTurnoverRatio
statistics.description: The average number of assists a player or team records per turnover

statistics.description: The number of times when the defense obtains the possession of the ball after a missed shot by the offense.

article.headline: Louisiana-Monroe 99, Southwest 70
article.story: MONROE, La. -- Rudy Turner scored 20 points, leading five Louisiana-Monroe players in double figures in a 99-70 rout of the University of the Southwest on Monday night. Dynile Forbes scored 19 points for the Warhawks (5-8), while Tony Hooper and Tommie Sykes chipped in 16 apiece. Lawrence Gilbert chipped in with 11 points. The Warhawks led just 43-40 against the Mustangs, and NAIA school that counted the game as an exhibition, with 1:44 to play in the opening half. But ULM went on a 7-0 run to take a 10-point halftime lead. The Mustangs stayed fairly close throughout the second half, but the Warhawks closed the game on a 10-0 run. They held the Mustangs scoreless for the final 3 minutes. ULM shot 83.3 percent from the free throw line (25-for-30) compared to a 65 percent mark for the Mustangs (13-for-20). Demetrius Evans led the Mustangs with 19 points.
